In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims September 27, 2016, as National Voter Registration Day. He emphasizes the importance of the right to vote and encourages all citizens to get involved in civic life by registering to vote. Obama highlights the need for citizens to fully participate in the democratic process and expresses concern about the number of eligible voters who choose not to participate. He mentions efforts to improve the voting process and make it easier for people to register, such as online registration and door-to-door voter registration campaigns. Obama urges Americans to not lose hope in the political process and emphasizes that the strength of the government depends on citizens exercising their right to vote. He concludes by calling upon all Americans to observe National Voter Registration Day by ensuring they are registered to vote.